    cpp:hasSMILES "N[C@@H](CC(C)C)C(=O)N[C@@H](CC(C)C)C(=O)N[C@@H]([C@@H](C)CC)C(=O)N[C@@H]([C@@H](C)CC)C(=O)N[C@@H](CC(C)C)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCN=C)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCN=C)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCN=C)C(=O)N[C@@H]([C@@H](C)CC)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCN=C)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCCN)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCC(=O)N)C(=O)N[C@@H](C)C(=O)N[C@@H](Cc1[nH]cnc1)C(=O)N[C@@H](C)C(=O)N[C@@H](CC1=NC=NC1)C(=O)N[C@@H](CO)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCCN)C(=O)O"^^xsd:string ;
    cpp:hasSequence "LLIILRRRIRKQAHAHSK"^^xsd:string ;
    cpp:hasUptakeEfficiency "1.5 times greater than the individual sum of the parts"@en,
        "Efficient delivery of ASO-1 into the bacterial cell."@en,
        "FITC-conjugated pVEC penetrated into C. reinhardtii in both the pVEC only treated group and pVEC and RNP-treated group"@en,
        "High"@en,
        "High level of translocation efficacy was observed in both types of fungal cells for peptides with a relatively high net charge (>=+4), including penetratin, pVEC, MAP, SynB, (KFF)_K, and MPG."@en,
        "Intracellular fluorescence was improved with R9-modified NPs compared to the PEN and pVEC which was confirmed by flow cytometry"@en,
        "LST_Pvec was slightly less effective than were other CPPs, it was still superior to parental LST"@en,
        "Lower internalization efficiency with values of 25% or less"@en,
        "No reduction of CFU per millilitre was observed in S. pyogenes strains. Also did not affect the survival of infected larvae."@en,
        "OBP::pVEC showed  Transduction efficiencies of 17.2% in liposomes."@en,
        "Penetration efficiency- 354.82345A.U."@en,
        "The uptake of all liposomal formulations increased on average from 33% to 71% in bEnd.3 cells, 35% to 66% in glial cells and In primary neuronal cells from 33% to 65%, were observed after 1 hour and 4 hours of incubation. TAT-Tf-liposomes containing chitosanâpGFP complexes induced significantly (p<0.05) higher GFP levels compared to pVec-Tf-lip and QL-Tf-lip (7.2% vs 4.2% and 2.8% GFP-expressing cells, respectively)."@en,
        "Translocation of pVEC-GFP led to 3.0 times as many GFP-positive cells compared to GFP only, and little effect with the linker."@en .

