    cpp:hasUptakeEfficiency "After 24 h, no fluorescence was detected in cells incubated with FITC-labeled 2PP7 VLPs and FTIC-labeled 2PP7-23b VLPs while with FITC-labeled 2PP7-TAT-23b VLPs exhibited a high level of fluorescence"@en,
        "At pH 6.5, however, a strong red signal was colocalized with lysosomes (green signal), thus indicating that PT-K-CAA possesses a higher internalization capacity than at pH 7.4"@en,
        "FA-TAT-Lip has a 66% increased uptake than TAT-Lip and 3.2 times than FA-Lip."@en,
        "HIV-TAT and HIV-gp41 showing the highest punctate percentages in 9L and 9L-R"@en,
        "Moderate uptake efficiency"@en,
        "PKT-S-PEG could enter cells efficiently in 2 h, which was similar to PKT, suggesting that PEG were degraded from dendrimer; in contrast, PKT-C-PEG showed inefficient entrance into cells due to the shielding of PEG chains. At the same time, no fluorescence signal was detected for P-S-PEG, Indicating that the dendrimer carriers could not enter cells at the concentration."@en .

