    cpp:hasSequence "VLTTGLPALISWIRRRHRRHC"^^xsd:string ;
    cpp:hasUptakeEfficiency "24 hours after p5RHH-p65 siRNA nanoparticle treatment p65 mRNA was reduced by 82% and was significantly higher than that of control cells with no treatment (p=6.38eâ8), cells treated with p5RHH-scrambled siRNA nanoparticles (p=1.60eâ7), and cells treated with free p65 siRNA (p=1.72eâ8)"@en,
        "Higher mRNA uptake efficiencies to Lipofectamine were observed for STR-Arg8 (83.7%), p5RHH (86.7%) and RALA (99.9%)-mediated mRNA complexes."@en,
        "NP could be seen penetrating human OA cartilage up to a depth of at least 700 Î¼m, freely diffusing into CHOndrocyte lacunae located in the intermediate zone"@en,
        "The expression of niRFP was clearly observed only after 48 h in the wire-injured artery but not in the contralateral uninjured artery of the same niRFP mRNA-p5RHH nanoparticle-treated mice"@en,
        "Tumors from the IP-injected mice had more intracellular fuorescence than those from IV-injected mice."@en,
        "p5RHH-siRNA NP was taken up by the CHOndrocytes but not free Cy3-labeled siRNA. And in HUVECs, Delivery of human p65 siRNA NP led to marked decrease in p65 expression exhibited similar or superior transfection efciency compared with Lipofectamine"@en .

