    cpp:hasUptakeEfficiency "0.04% of the given dose of free TETA was recovered in brain tissue, while 0.63% (16-fold increase in brain uptake) could be recovered from brain tissue when TETA was encapsulated in vectorized liposomes"@en,
        "14C-mannitol permeability was enhanced 10.5 fold with T-penetratin"@en,
        "15-fold increase over background of untreated cells and TAMRA delivery follows P17â>>P11â=âP14â>âP40â=âArg9â>âtatâ=âpenetratin"@en,
        "70-fold increase in eGFP fluorescence"@en,
        "Able to penetrate PC-3 cells at 5 mM concentration"@en,
        "Apparent permeability coefficients= 4.54 Â± 2.01 Ã 10â6 (cm/s)"@en,
        "At 0.25 to 2.5 mM, the membrane permeation property of TATp-D was significantly higher than that of R8, Penetratin, and TATp"@en,
        "Both P7-Arg11 and P7-Pen [but not Pen and Arg11 or P7 without CPP], significantly reduced LPS-mediated IFNÎ² and TNF mRNA expression), with P7-Pen being the most potent inhibitor."@en,
        "Both showed similar internalization potency"@en,
        "Cellular uptake of NPs-1 was â¼68% higher than that of NCs, 52% higher for NPs-2 than NPs-1 and 36% higher for NPs-3 than NPs-2."@en,
        "Curcumin-loaded conjugate 1 micelles was significantly higher"@en,
        "Did not show any penetration"@en,
        "Effect of L-penetratin on epithelial permeation of insulin was stronger than that of D-R8"@en,
        "Effectively delivered protein"@en,
        "FITC fluorescence intensity of RGD/R8-DDP/ERG-LIP was higher than that of DDP/ERG-LIP, R8-DDP/ERG-LIP, and RGD-DDP/ERG-LIP."@en,
        "Fl-Pen were efficiently taken up by both 3T3-L1 and stromal vascular fraction (SVF)-derived primary adipocytes . Fl-Pen-X-ACIP was efficiently taken up by two different human adipocyte cell lines and effective in human cancer cachexia treatment."@en,
        "High"@en,
        "High level of translocation efficacy"@en,
        "High preference for the outer cell layers"@en,
        "High uptake efficiency"@en,
        "Higher degradation rate"@en,
        "Higher internalization than other peptides."@en,
        "Higher than R9, Tat and R6L3"@en,
        "Higher than Tat"@en,
        "Higher uptake efficiency for BSA"@en,
        "Higher uptake of AntpOVA compared to OVA alone"@en,
        "In MDCKMDR cell model, penetratin-NP presented enhanced cel- lular accumulation"@en,
        "Increase in Papp of the drug was observed when DexSP was co-delivered with PEN (1.3 Â± 0.2 x10-5 cm/s)"@en,
        "Internalisation rate of Cf-Penetratin, Cf-Dhvar4 and Cf-Melittin was the highest"@en,
        "Intracellular fluorescence was improved with R9-modified NPs compared to the PEN and pVEC which was confirmed by flow cytometry"@en,
        "KTP@MnO2 show penetration efficiencies of 14.4% and 30.1% at 3h and 6 h."@en,
        "L- and D-PenetraMax show greatest increase in ileum insulin absorption than other CPP"@en,
        "L- and D-penetratin significantly increases the epithelial permeation of MTX and VCR"@en,
        "L-penetratin (2mM) enhanced the systemic absorption of both GLP-1 and exendin-4."@en,
        "LMWP group had stronger fluorescence, followed by penetratin, TAT and R8 groups"@en,
        "Less permeability than PenetraMax"@en,
        "Less than polyarginine but greater tha Tat and tra"@en,
        "Low"@en,
        "Lower efficiency"@en,
        "Lower internalization efficiency with values of 32%"@en,
        "Lower than CyLoP1"@en,
        "Lower uptake efficiency"@en,
        "Mean AF647 fluorescence per cell increased with the Penetratin-SpyCatcher fusion protein versus the SpyCatcher alone."@en,
        "Nanoparticles functionalized with TAT were taken up at a higher intensity with PNT nanoparticles"@en,
        "No significant difference in the level of intracellular biotin with either Biotin-P16 or Biotin-P7."@en,
        "P16 sequence efficiently deliver the bioactive cargo to produce a functional inhibitory response"@en,
        "PEN-SOD1 internalization was comparable to TAT-SOD1 and R10- SOD1"@en,
        "Pen-CS-NLC, the percentage of transported NPs was found to be 33 %."@en,
        "Penetratin (Ant) did not support antisense PNA uptake into S. pyogenes. Also did not affect the survival of infected larvae."@en,
        "Penetratin, showed a low cellular uptake of 28.7%"@en,
        "Penetration efficiency- 339.30845A.U."@en,
        "PepB2 show greater efficacy than other"@en,
        "Positive influence on the internalization efficiency"@en,
        "R8 and Tat increased the uptake of 200-nm nanoparticles by Caco-2 cells to 2.1-3.0 times that was similar or superior than penetratin and PenetraMax"@en,
        "Show considerably lower uptake"@en,
        "Similar uptake was observed for the QD625 labeled peptide as of pAntp"@en,
        "Superior IgG response than TAT"@en,
        "TAMRA labelling improves penetration to a larger degree than MSe labelling"@en,
        "TAMRAâpenetratin demonstrated only a modest degree of lysosomal colocalization (47.3 Â± 3.3%, mean + S.E.M.) after 30 min"@en,
