        "Tf-Pen-liposomes (20.8 ± 4.0 ng/_g of protein) significantly (p < 0.05) increased ApoE expression in the brain of mice compared to unmodified liposomes (14.4 ± 3.4 ng/_g of protein), naked plasmid ApoE2 (3.4 ± 1.8 ng/_g of protein) and endogenous ApoE levels (2.5 ± 2.0 ng/_g of protein)."@en,
        "The ANTP-SmacN7 fusion protein successfully entered and accumulated in the cells."@en,
        "The OA-g-CS-PEN-MAN/pApoE2 polyplex demonstrated significantly (p < 0.05) 10.9 times higher transfection of pApoE2 in the primary astrocytes over naked pApoE2. And in mice was â1.63 times higher."@en,
        "The Uptake of TAMRA-insulin was higher for the D-PEN than L-PEN at both pH 6.5 and 7.4."@en,
        "The fluorescence intensity of the cells treated with Ru@Pen@PEG-AuNS was stronger and dose-dependent than that of the cells treated with Ru@PEG-AuNS."@en,
        "The internalization of PenTf-liposomes was significantly higher (p<0.001) compared to Plain-, Tf- and Pen-liposome in bEnd.3 cells at 4 h and also percent uptake is higher than astrocytes and primary neuronal cells."@en,
        "The mono-cyclic G7-peptides (G7-18NATE-Pen and G7-M2-Pen) are clearly superior in cellular uptake than the bicyclic peptides (G7-B7-Pen and/or G7-B7M2-Pen) while G7-18NATE without Pen does not internalize inside cells."@en,
        "The percentages of fluorescence-positive cells in both PG5/ASO and PG5/ASO/Pene groups were more than three-fold higher over that of the naked ASO group"@en,
        "The uptake of 5-FU loaded Tf-Pen-conjugated liposomes was found to be 66.64 Â± 3.00% and 59.68 Â± 4.55% in U87 and bEnd.3 cells, respectively, which was significantly higher than single ligand (47.66 Â± 1.78 % and 46.28 Â± 2.39 % respectively for Tf and 45.91 Â± 4.62 and 43.42 Â± 2.31 respectively for Pen) or plain liposomes (31.51 Â± 2.92% and 28.56 Â± 3.29% respectively)."@en,
        "The uptake of Dox and Elro-loaded liposomes showed more than 73% of cellular uptake in all three types of cells, which further confirmed the efficacy of Tf-Pen liposomes over single ligand or plain liposomes.Rapid and higher uptake of Tf-Pen liposomes in U87 cells compared to bEnd.3 and glial cells."@en,
        "Three CPPs (TAT, penetratin and R8) showed the highest internalization profiles in both cell types.Penetratin crossed the intestinal barrier."@en,
        "Uptake in all the four cell lines has the general trend of Transportan>R8>PenetratinâTAT>Xentry"@en,
        "Uptake of Alexa 488 labelled pAntp was 1.7 Â± 0.3 Ã 10â 18 moles/cell"@en,
        "d-penetratin results in an increase by a factor of three than r9"@en,
        "r9 and pen had outperformed their L-analogues"@en .

