    cpp:hasUptakeEfficiency "KAibA-MC was significantly more effective than Tat-MC in transfection. KAibA/EED4-MC and KAibA/LAH4-L1-MC had higher uptake efficiency than KAibA/GALA-MC but  all exhibited lower efficiency than the CPP-modified micelle (KAibA-MC).while KAibA/EED4-MC and KAibA/LAH4-L1-MC exhibited significantly higher transfection efficiency than KAibA-MC, while KAibA/GALA-MC demonstrated comparable efficiency to a control (naked pDNA)"@en,
        "The transfection efficiency of the clustered plasmid DNA/CTP/CPP complexes gradually increased (up to 7.6 times, 2.7 times in average) in Arabidopsis leaves at 24â72 h after spraying compared to plasmid DNA molecules or plasmid DNA/CTP complexes formed at N/P ratio = 1.0."@en,
        "cpPD-Cy3 complexes penetrate into cells and chloroplasts within 6 h after their infiltration into the extracellular space."@en .

