    cpp:hasSequence "YGRKKRRQRRRC"^^xsd:string ;
    cpp:hasUptakeEfficiency "24 h after injections, the LACP group still displayed high intensity of fluorescence in the tumor tissue, whereas other groups(CP, lipo2000/CP, and ACP groups) showed no fluorescence in the tumors."@en,
        "Approximately 1.56 and 2.17 folds increase than PTX/FITC or  PTX-LNA"@en,
        "Compared with NP-C6, AT-NP-C6 have higher cellular uptake in  MCF-7 cells."@en,
        "Dose dependent uptake"@en,
        "Efficient penetratation"@en,
        "Higher uptake efficiency"@en,
        "Highest fluorescence intensity was detected in HUVECs treated with exosomes, treated with FITC-Tat-PEG (5 k)-DPPE, among other Tat-PEG (20, 40 k)-DPPEs."@en,
        "Ramos cells expected high fluorescence intensity, while HeLa cells showed no apparent fluorescent intensity for ATNP and ANP, which might be due to the specificity of aptamer to Ramos cells. HeLa cells treated with ATNP and TNP showed obvious fluorescence intensity due to the uptake of DNA nanopore in the help of TAT peptide, while for the ANP and FNP, no apparent fluorescent intensity was observed."@en,
        "Second highest in transduction"@en,
        "The CSâpVGF polyplex was a minor transfecting complex against all three types of cells, while OA-g-CS-Man-TatâpVGF was the most transfecting polyplex."@en,
        "The transfection rate of C6 cells with free pDNA, pDNA-(ss)373 LPNPs, Ang-pDNA-(ss)373 LPNPs, Ang-TAT-pDNA-(ss)373 LPNPs, and Ang-TAT-Fe3O4-pDNA-(ss)373 LPNPs was 0.143%, 1.51%, 5.20%, 8.23%, and 14.6% at 24 h respectively,"@en .

