    cpp:hasUptakeEfficiency "Accumulation increased 2-fold with NPh-Ce6-NGR-R7 and approximately 1.5-fold with the NPh-Ce6, as compared with free chlorin e6."@en,
        "Cells treated with coumarin-6-CNPs + R7 showed stronger green fluorescence than cells treated with coumarin-6-CNPs."@en,
        "High (relative to Tat (49-57))"@en,
        "Higher uptake efficiency"@en,
        "Penetration efficiency- 806.194275A.U."@en,
        "Photo-irradiation enhanced the cellular uptake by 1.1 to 3-fold for FITC-R7E7 concentrations between 10 and 100 mM, respectively"@en,
        "Significantly effective compared to the other poly-arginines"@en,
        "The LPNVTat and LPNVArg7 only surrounded the ER when they were dispersed in the cytosol, implying that Tat and Arg7 could lead the NVs towards the ER and nucleus but did not assist their penetration through the ER membrane."@en,
        "The intracellular distribution of Rh-123-R7/PSD-Fol NPs was relatively more than Rh-123-R7 NPs according to the green fluorescence distribution in MCF-7 and MCF-7/Adr cell."@en,
        "selzR7 showed a significantly higher (P < 0.05) uptake number of phages than WT selz in A549 cells."@en .

