    cpp:hasUptakeEfficiency "(FITC)-labeled Tat-SIRT5-CTM was effectively distributed in hippocampal and cortical tissues"@en,
        "14C-mannitol permeability was enhanced 3.8 fold with T-Tat47â57"@en,
        "2% of PTD-DeRed and 7% of PTD-J-DeRed transduce into cells with 40âÎ¼g/mL"@en,
        "3T3-L1 cells to be >10-fold higher than in HEK293 cells"@en,
        "46 % of transported shown by Tat-CS coated NLC(Tat-CS-NLC ), higher than CS-NLC and NLC (*p < 0.05)(NLC"@en,
        "5nm AuNPs-CPP-FITC showed a strong fluorescence signal throughout the cells  while10 nm AuNPs (AuNPs-CPP-FITC) were not internalized."@en,
        "61.5 Â± 4.8% of the FITC-labeled TAT-KR-12-treated RAW264.7 cells exhibited fluorescence, which is much higher than the result of FITC-KR-12 treated cells (22.4 Â± 3.5%)."@en,
        "80% of the cells were observed to be transduced with 50 Î¼g/ml of TAT-HA-HDAg-L(198-210) fusion protein."@en,
        "80.07Â±1.16 internalization percentages of the cells treated with 5 Î¼M TAT"@en,
        "After 2 hours incubation, fluorescent of TDCS-Tat NPs was remarkably stronger than the other four NPs (TDCS-Pen NPs, TDCS-R8 NPs, TDCS NPs and PVA NPs)."@en,
        "At pH 6.8 for 3 h, the blue fluorescence from mPEG-HCPT-loaded PECL/DA-Tat-M enhanced significantly, and the mean fluorescence intensity was 10 times higher than that of groups incubated at pH 7.4."@en,
        "Both GST-TAT and GST-TAT-rpS3(E9) proteins were detected in the inside of cells"@en,
        "Both TAT-IL-24-KDEL and TAT-IL-24 transfected T24 cells with the efficiency of 97.3% and 96.5%, whereas nearly no green fluorescence was observed in IL-24-treated cells."@en,
        "Both the TAT-fused peptides, 1 and 2, were able to penetrate the cell membrane and reached the area of cytosol and nucleus compartments."@en,
        "CBS_E2 was readily delivered into cells while in the absence of TAT_CaM negligible signal"@en,
        "CVP1-N2 showed more efficient cellular uptake than CVP1 and TAT"@en,
        "Cells expressing both NRP1 and HS proteoglycans robustly internalized AgNP-TAT-OH"@en,
        "Compared with L, the uptakes of TL, PL and PTL by MCs in vitro were increased to 154.4%, 163.8% and 200.7%, respectively."@en,
        "Concentration- and time-dependent internalization"@en,
        "Conjugation to TAT facilitates efficient internalisation of the peptides"@en,
        "Conjugation with peptide Tat could enhance by 1.2â2.2 times cellular uptake on varied explosion time (0â2 h) relative to Fe3O4@SiO2-Amino NPs,"@en,
        "Cy3 fluorescence of TAT-S19-Ago2 in cells was higher than that of TAT-Ago2"@en,
        "Delivery efficiency of CPP-DNA conjugates was almost similar to that of SLO."@en,
        "Displayed 48.6 % EGFP gene expression"@en,
        "Dose dependent uptake"@en,
        "Dose-and time dependent internalization"@en,
        "Efficient cellular uptake of the CPP conjugated peptides was confirmed by immunofluorescent labelling with FITC, bound with EphA2, blocked ANXA1 binding EphA2, and targeted EphA2 degradation."@en,
        "Efficiently penetrate cell membranes within a few hours"@en,
        "Enhanced permeability"@en,
        "FITC-labelled PTD-p37 showed that 40 to 50 % of cells were incorporated with p37 at 48 , 72 or 96 h post-treatment with PTD-p37 and almost no p37 was detected with FITC-conjugated p37."@en,
        "Fluorescence intensities for TAT- and R9-CBD3-treated cells were greater than those for MTS- and MAP-CBD3-treated cells"@en,
        "For DOX/GA@ TAT-M Compared to those at pH 7.4, the uptakes at pH 6.4 were enhanced by 2.6-fold, 1.5-fold, and 3.1-fold for 1, 2, and 4 h incubation, respectively."@en,
        "GFP protein was in the cells only treated with TAT-rpS3(E9)-GFP"@en,
        "GST-TAT-SOD was successfully delivered into cells, whereas wild SOD was not."@en,
        "HIV-TAT(47â57) was unable to transport BSA or Trastuzumab"@en,
        "High"@en,
        "Higher Ig2a was found in TAT-Ag85B group than only Ag85B vaccination"@en,
        "Higher penetration compared with LCN-FITC"@en,
        "Higher uptake efficiency"@en,
        "Highest cellular uptake than that of SAP and SA."@en,
        "In all the four different cell lines tested, namely HeLa (cervix), MCF-7 (breast), Hep G2 (liver), and A549 (lung), 1% DMSO showed a drastic increase for the nucleus targeting of QDs-Tat (increase from â¼5% to â¼55%)"@en,
        "Internalization increase rapidly in the first 2 min and then slow down between 2 and 30 min"@en,
        "Low"@en,
        "Lower than penetratin and R6W4"@en,
        "Lower uptake efficiency"@en,
        "Lycosin-I and TAT showed comparable intracellular internalization with an increase at least 26 times than without CPP."@en,
        "More active than that of A1"@en,
        "No difference in the intracellular distribution of PNIPAM and PNIPAM-TAT particles"@en,
        "Penetrating capacity of PFV and VPT were much lower than TAT while it was higher for CsA."@en,
        "Penetration efficiency- 2712.6005A.U."@en,
        "Polyplexes functionalized with the TAT peptide, the fluorescence is higher when compared with non-functionalized polyplexes, indicating a greater cellular and time-dependent internalization"@en,
        "Rapid delivery in under ten minute"@en,
        "Rapid uptake of CPP through endosomes as Fluorescent vesicles were observed in as little as 20 min."@en,
        "Recombinant PTD-p38WT has constitutive kinase activity and can penetrate NPCs."@en,
        "Showed a 2-fold higher higher permeabilities than control with more in cornea."@en,
        "Showed increased uptake efficiency"@en,
        "Showed significantly higher permeability than FD-7"@en,
        "Significantly higher level of total p53 (2.5-fold in Huh7 or 2.6-fold in L02 cells) with PTD-p53 compared to control cells."@en,
        "Specific and strong labeling of the platelet population with CPP conjugate MB."@en,
        "Strong fluorescence signal was observed inside the cells incubated with TAT-gelonin, indicating rapid and efficient transduction of TAT-gelonin mediated by TAT"@en,
        "Successfully deliver of the Ab into the cells."@en,
        "TAMRA labelling improves penetration to a larger degree than MSe labelling"@en,
        "TAMRA-Tat exhibited significantly better BBB permeation (32.21 Â± 10.17 F/F0 * min) compared to TAMRA-Tat-NR2B9c (5.54 Â± 2.95 F/F0 * min) and TAMRA-Tat-N-dimer (6.90 Â± 3.90 F/F0 *"@en,
        "TAT a 1-fold increase in permeability efficiency over RWRWR"@en,
        "TAT and ARG demonstrated higher permeability efficiencies compared to OWRWR and RWRWR"@en,
        "TAT complexes led to high ND1 levels when compared to control cells"@en,
        "TAT efficiently delivered PHDP5 to hippocampus."@en,
        "TAT-2CPT displayed stronger cell-penetrating activity than TAT-CPT."@en,
        "TAT-Au-Dox treated cells had significantly greater mean fluorescence intensity as compared to free Dox alone for all tested concentrations (p < 0.05 for 50 nM; p < 0.001 for 100, 200, and 500 nM)"@en,
        "TAT-Cx43266â283-B was internalized by astrocytes and more efficiently by GSCs, but not significantly by neurons"@en,
        "TAT-EGFP successfully transduce HEK-293 and LNCaP cells while no fluorescence detected in the cells treated with EGFP without TAT sequence"@en,
        "TAT-LepFNR permanence inside the cell is shorter compared to TAT-LepHO."@en,
        "TAT-MnSOD wt led to the increase in the intracellular enzymatic activity of MnSOD, while the Inactive TAT-MnSOD mutant failed in induction of the intracellular enzymatic activity of MnSOD."@en,
        "TAT-PEG-ASA-MNP-CDDP in all 4 kinds of cells showed the highest fluorescence intensity with a significant average increased cellular uptake of 74% compared to CDDP alone."@en,
        "TAT-SAPIP not only penetrates the cell membrane but also decreases SrcâPSD-95 association."@en,
        "TAT-dependent uptake of both pAKT1 variants."@en,
        "TAT-hMT1A construct without the MTS was found only in the cytosol and its levels decreased"@en,
        "TG2 containing PTD (TG2P and TG2P (-LPS)) were readily internalized into the T cells and was as stable as endogenous TAGLN2 for at least 24 h."@en,
        "TMVRB-TAT5 showed 2-2.5-fold uptake efficiency compared with that of TMVRB at each time point for both HeLa cells and SMCs"@en,
        "Tat and R9 were ~2-fold less efficiently than cF_R4"@en,
        "Tat brush polymer promoted significant levels of Cre delivery"@en,
        "Tat-A1E28 and Tat-A4V48 co-localized most with early endosomes (EEA1) and lysosomes as evidenced by yellow spots. While Tat-E28 showed minimal localization, and no uptake or co-localization was observed for E28."@en,
        "Tat-A86 exhibited the best cell binding and uptake activities of miRNA in LLC cells compared to other ELPs."@en,
        "Tat-Hsp27 can be delivered into cells in a concentration-dependent manner"@en,
        "Tat-JDlys exhibited a greater ability to kill intracellular MRSA strains than JDlys, indicating that Tat could deliver JDlys into keratinocytes, while, neither Ant-JDlys nor Tp10-JDlys could eliminate intracellular MRSA."@en,
        "Tatibody(TAT + antibody) internalization potency is 3.6 fold higher than pertuzumab"@en,
        "Tf-TAT liposomes showed more than 70 % of cellular uptake of Dox and Erlo in U87, bEnd.3 and glial cells, while the plain liposomes had only ~ 30 % of uptake.Tf-TAT liposomes showed non-significantly higher transport as compared to Tf-QLPVM liposomes."@en,
        "The cellular uptake rate of MWCNTs-TC were moderately higher (84.69%Â±5.03%) than that of MWCNTs-CS (72.85%Â±4.95%)."@en,
        "The internalization of AgNPs coated with either TAT-NH2 or D-TAT was only sensitive to soluble HS competition, not to NRP1 blockade"@en,
        "The micelles PSPT-90 displayed 4 to 6 fold higher overall MFI compared to non conjugated PSPT-0."@en,
        "The signal was ~2-fold higher for PLGAÐVPÐTAT NPs than for the untargeted NPs (p = 0.009)"@en,
        "The uptake of all liposomal formulations increased on average from 33% to 71% in bEnd.3 cells, 35% to 66% in glial cells and In primary neuronal cells from 33% to 65%, waereobserved after 1 hour and 4 hours of incubation."@en,
        "Time- and concentration-dependent internalization"@en,
        "Time-dependent (15 min to 2 h) internalization"@en,
        "Transported EGFP into the Cytoplasm in great amount and even into the nucleus partly."@en,
        "Unable to penetrate PC-3 cells at 5 mM concentartion"@en,
        "Uptake in all the four cell lines has the general trend of Transportan>R8>PenetratinâTAT>Xentry"@en,
        "uptake of the mSWC (Man-CD/WT (mSWC)) nano complex was significantly higher than that of SWC (CD/WT (SWC)), which indicated that mannose targeting increases the uptake of nano complex. The increasing positive rate and MFI (Mean Fluorescence Intensity) of SWC and mSWC depended on the effect of TAT."@en,
        "~3 times higher than the cell brightness labelled with R8-Pdots and ~10,000 times higher in MCF-7 cells than MSC cells"@en .

