    cpp:hasUptakeEfficiency "(Arg)9 contained dFv-R-LDP showed apparent improvement in the penetration efficacy compared to dFv-R-LDP which displayed limited internalization in 1 h."@en,
        "(Arg)9-GST-SH2 TrM showed highest green fluorescence signal than (Arg)9-GST or (Arg)9-GST SH2 Wt"@en,
        "46% that of R9"@en,
        "ARG a 2-fold increase in permeability efficiency over RWRWR"@en,
        "Among fluorescent H-NPs, C-NPs and H Ã¾ C-NPs, fluorescence intensity of fluorescent H Ã¾ C-NPs was most significant to show the synergistic effect"@en,
        "Arg9 also slowed Ca2+ uptake, albeit to a lesser extent than Arg11,"@en,
        "B-mR9/pDNA polyplex had high transfection efficiency compared to the conventional linear R9 and mR9 CPP."@en,
        "BR2-siRNA-delivery efficiency was 2-fold higher than that of R9"@en,
        "Both P16 and the derivative P16b6 could inhibit the replication of RABV with dosage effect suggesting that the CPP was efcient in intracellular delivery of antiviral peptides."@en,
        "Cationic CPPs demonstrate the highest binding as compared to amphipathic ones"@en,
        "Co-localization of the R9-HuscFv99 and the native NS5A, which appeared in yellow/orange after merging at different levels of the cell sections, are seen."@en,
        "Cy5-labeled miR-139-5p was selectively delivered to tumor site by Ce6-R9-125I-RGD-MNPs with high efficiency in a cell-selective manner."@en,
        "D-R9 showed significantly greater efficiencies than BP100."@en,
        "Delivered PNA705 much better than tat  and TAMRA delivery follows P17â>>P11â=âP14â>âP40â=âArg9â>âtatâ=âpenetratin"@en,
        "Delivery efficiency of miR-34a into HepG2, MCF-7 and A549 cells was much lower than that into HeLa or KB cells."@en,
        "Dual fluorescence signals of RhB-R9H6-QD in both the intracellular and extracellular regions"@en,
        "Efficient uptake of the linear peptide"@en,
        "Elevated FITC signal through flow cytometry proving dendritic cells successfully phagocytized the bacterial complex."@en,
        "Enhance uptake of AgNP"@en,
        "Enhanced the cell penetration and endosome release of CPPs."@en,
        "FISH-TAMB probes were successfully delivered into the cells"@en,
        "Fluorescence intensities for TAT- and R9-CBD3-treated cells were greater than those for MTS- and MAP-CBD3-treated cells"@en,
        "Fluorescence intensity of EXO-R9 group was about 6.03-fold higher than EXO group"@en,
        "GFP intensity with EGFP-9R was higher than that in EGFP-treated cells"@en,
        "Greater than r9"@en,
        "HSA-plasmid-R9 nanoparticles exhibited a higher transfection efficiency(53.1+- 30.0%) compared to spontaneous transfection upon incubation with free DNA or the negative HSA-plasmid-PEG control with negligible cellular uptake."@en,
        "High"@en,
        "High (relative to Tat (49-57))"@en,
        "Higher cellular internalization of R9-CmLN than of CmLN"@en,
        "Higher than peptide 1"@en,
        "Higher uptake efficiency"@en,
        "Intracellular fluorescence intensity gradually increased with increasing incubation time and APTstat3-9R concentration, reaching a maximum at 4 h. Also, [FITC-APTstat3-9R]- DLNPs exhibited a greater fluorescence signal in deeper layers of the skin in normal mouse ear skin treated compared with skin treated with FITC-APTstat3- 9R alone."@en,
        "Intracellular fluorescence was improved with R9-modified NPs compared to the PEN and pVEC which was confirmed by flow cytometry"@en,
        "K9 demonstrated relatively high penetration efficiency (approximately 80%) in N. benthamiana leaves"@en,
        "Low"@en,
        "Low transfection efficiencies"@en,
        "Lower efficiency"@en,
        "Lower than penetratin and R6W3"@en,
        "Lower uptake efficiency"@en,
        "Lower uptake efficiency than D form"@en,
        "More efficient in provoking bud formation"@en,
        "More than 20 fold cumulative amount of DFS penetrating through the mice skin with r9-SA than that of the negative control."@en,
        "No significant difference between aR8W1 and R9"@en,
        "Penetration efficiency- 2056.881568A.U."@en,
        "Peptide 3 was 2.5 to 17 times higher than that of R9"@en,
        "PolyR and Trans penetrated into an average area of 70 ± 4% of telencephalon"@en,
        "Positive influence on the internalization efficiency"@en,
        "Possesses excellent photothermal transduction efficacy"@en,
        "R9 has the best effect on enhancing QD delivery than  QD alone"@en,
        "R9 nanocomplexes were capable of successfully transfecting HeLa cells with pGL4.17 at an N/P ratio of 30 or higher"@en,
        "R9 uptake was about five times higher than r9 uptake"@en,
        "R9/GFP complexes can be taken up by cells"@en,
        "SOMV-9RE7 treated group showed the highest splenocyte activation compared to SOMV alone"@en,
        "Signal intensities with 7D12-Atto532"@en,
        "Significantly promoted intracellular copper delivery"@en,
        "Strong fluorescent signal was detected in cells treated with SR9/QD complexes."@en,
        "TAMRA-labeled dR9 exhibited higher penetration efficiency into the palisade mesophyll than the other CPPs examined."@en,
        "TAT and ARG demonstrated higher permeability efficiencies compared to OWRWR and RWRWR"@en,
        "The R9-HuscFvs of all clones were found to be cell penetrable, and they were located predominantly in the cytoplasm."@en,
        "The cellular uptake of NPs significantly increased in both bEnd.3 and U87-MG cells exhibited a dose-dependent cellular uptake fter 4 h of incubation compared to T7 peptide-free PP5k NPs."@en,
        "The efficiency of dTat-Sar-EED4 was up to â¼20-fold higher than dTat , R9 and BP100"@en,
        "The fluorescent images at less than or equal to 5 microM peptides show that the peptide can access the cell interior at a variety of concentrations and within 2 h of dosing."@en,
        "The mean fluorescence intensity of 9R-Hsp27 was 26.8"@en,
        "Time- and concentration-dependent internalization"@en,
        "Time-dependent internalization"@en,
        "Transduction lower than HR9"@en,
        "UNC7938-induced cell penetration was overall more efficient for dfTAT and D-dfTAT than for TMR-TAT and r12"@en,
        "Uptake of ASOs was more than 10-fold higher in cells that were incubated with PF14 polyplexes compared with R9 polyplexes or naked ASOs"@en,
        "Uptake of R5W3R4 peptide is better than R9 and [RW]6"@en,
        "Vesicular fluorescence was presented that further increased to an N/P ratio of 5"@en,
