    cpp:hasUptakeEfficiency "1 microMolar uptake in HeLa cells relative to TAT 1 _M"@en,
        "87% of EV were FITC-positive when FAM-labelled TAT-LL37-VHHm3F was incubated with EV"@en,
        "All mtDFOs showed good Rr values ranging from +0.45 to +0.68, meaning that they all entered Mitochondria"@en,
        "CCI NPs displayed a large number of stained myocardial cells, showing enhanced uptake through CPPs and CRT modification. Also , the fluorescent intensities of CCI NPs were significantly enhanced, and those of CCI NPs were 2.96-fold that of CON NPs in the mice model."@en,
        "CPP-KR12 showed a 2-fold increase in fluorescence intensity relative to KR12 in Gram-negative bacteria."@en,
        "Dose-dependent internalizaion"@en,
        "Enhanced permeability"@en,
        "High"@en,
        "Higher cell internalization for UTriCOOHPhOâTAT compared to UTriCOOHPhOH"@en,
        "Low"@en,
        "Lower efficiency"@en,
        "Lower than CyLoP1"@en,
        "Most TAT-NDUFS8 and NDUFS8-TAT l found to be within T-REx-293 cells whereas no NDUFS8 signal without TAT"@en,
        "No enhanced transfection efficiency than VAMP8"@en,
        "Penetration efficiency- 2837.4715A.U."@en,
        "Rapid intracellular uptake of the fusion protein (full-length TOE1-EGFP) but not of the control EGFP alone."@en,
        "Strong fluorescence of PNA-Tat and PNA-R8 than PNA-MK3"@en,
        "T-MNS (ICG) exhibited considerably stronger fluorescent signals compared to those treated with controls."@en,
        "TAT had no significant effect on Ca2+ uptake."@en,
        "TAT-GFP dose of 15 mg/kg in mice resulted in GFP primarily accumulating in colon after 4 h"@en,
        "TAT-PTD increased uptake and partitioning of a fluorescent marker TAMRA."@en,
        "TAT-SOD1 and R10-SOD1 could efficiently enter cells."@en,
        "TAT-cAMP sponge transduced into human sperm."@en,
        "Tat spread into 27 ±13% of the telencephalon"@en,
        "Tat(49â57) were the least efficient CPPs in BY-2 cells"@en,
        "Tat-C-RP7 was a more potent penetrating peptide than Tat"@en,
        "The bright blue fluorescence was observed in 356-AuNPs and 356-TAT-AuNPs group, these figures indicated that 356 TAT-AuNPs entered HCT-116 cells effectively. The amounts of Au treated with 356-TAT-AuNPs were 3.1-fold higher than the 356-AuNPs treated group after incubation with 24 h."@en,
        "The intracellular levels of Tat-SOD transduced at 3 Î¼M in the cells were rapidly and markedly upregulated up to 120 min"@en,
        "Time-dependent internalization"@en,
        "Transfection efficiency of F-2pDNA (TAT-OL nanoemulsion formulation 2) was enhanced by 1.76-fold and 1.67-fold in comparison to F-1pDNA (TAT-OL nanoemulsion formulation 1) and Lipofectin"@en,
        "Tri-Tat A shows homogeneous cytosolic uptake and nucleolar staining at 1_M while mono-Tat and tri-Tat B showed no evidence of cytosolic uptake or nucleolar staining"@en .

