    cpp:hasSMILES "N[C@@H](CC1=C(C(=NC1)C)CC)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCC(=O)O)C(=O)N[C@@H](C)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCN=C)C(=O)N[C@@H](CC(C)C)C(=O)N[C@@H](C)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCN=C)C(=O)N[C@@H](C)C(=O)N[C@@H](CC(C)C)C(=O)N[C@@H](C)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCN=C)C(=O)N[C@@H](C)C(=O)N[C@@H](CC(C)C)C(=O)N[C@@H](C)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCN=C)C(=O)N[C@@H](Cc1[nH]cnc1)C(=O)N[C@@H](CC(C)C)C(=O)N[C@@H](C)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCN=C)C(=O)N[C@@H](C)C(=O)N[C@@H](CC(C)C)C(=O)N[C@@H](C)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCN=C)C(=O)N[C@@H](C)C(=O)N[C@@H](CC(C)C)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCN=C)C(=O)N[C@@H](C)C(=O)N[C@@H](CS)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCC(=O)O)C(=O)N[C@@H](C)C(=O)O"^^xsd:string ;
    cpp:hasSequence "WEARLARALARALARHLARALARALRACEA"^^xsd:string ;
    cpp:hasUptakeEfficiency "4.9, 56.3 and 28.9% of mCherry-positive cells and 14.6, 86.5 and 29.5% of EGFP-positive cells were observed in the STR-Arg8, p5RHH and RALA complexes treatment groups, respectively in CT26.CL25 cancer cells."@en,
        "Cells transfected with FITC-RALA/Cy3-pDNA nanoparticles rapidly accumulate and retain both fluorophores up to 1440 min following transfection."@en,
        "Complex pPSCA to RALA resulted in significantly higher transfection efficacies at N:P ratios 4 and 10, in HEK-293 cells and DC 2.4 cells respectively, compared to using naked pPSCA (N:P 0) alone."@en,
        "FKBPL knockdown and overexpression was observed from 0.125 Î¼g siFKBPL and 1 Î¼g pFKBPL, respectively, when delivered with RALA."@en,
        "In normal low glucose the cellular uptake significantly increased from 20.0 Â± 3.4% to 66.5 Â± 3.1% (p Ë 0.001), with increasing siRNA concentration from 20 to 80 nmol/L"@en,
        "MDA-MB-231 internalize FITC-RALA/BP nanoparticles more rapidly than PC3s"@en,
        "RALA enabling the strongest mRNA uptake, RGSG the lowest, and RRRR an intermediate"@en,
        "RALA-E6/E7 NPs successfully transfected NCTC-929 cells as demonstrated by over expression of both HPV-16 E6 and HPV-16 E7 antigens compared to untreated cells"@en,
        "RALA/pDNA carrier  N/P ratios of 5 and 10 are internalized at a higher extent than N/P ratio of 2"@en,
        "RALA/pDNA nanoparticles in vitro is comparable with commercial transfecting agents while exhibiting significantly lower cytotoxicity"@en,
        "RALA/pEGFP-N1 nanoparticles at a N:P ratio of 6, transfection efficiency was 33.7+_ 1.65% in HMEC-1 endothelial cells"@en,
        "The FACS analysis showed that the transfection rates were 11.5%, 19.0%, 62.4%, and 10.3% in Group 2 (siEGFR + US), Group 5 (NBsiEGFR + US), Group 6 (CPP-NBsiEGFR + US) and Group 7 (CPP-NBsiEGFR), respectively,"@en,
        "Transfection efficiency of RALA group was less than 40% in HEK-293T cell and 25% in HeLa cells."@en,
        "pDNA transfection of RALA group was above 60% in HeLa cells."@en .

