    cpp:hasIonicState "Cationic"@en ;
    cpp:hasLength 22 ;
    cpp:hasLinearity "Linear"@en ;
    cpp:hasSMILES "N[C@@H](CCCCN)C(=O)N[C@@H]([C@@H](C)CC)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCCN)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCCN)C(=O)N[C@@H](C(C)C)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCCN)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCCN)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCCN)C(=O)NCC(=O)N[C@@H](CCCN=C)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCCN)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCCN)C(=O)N[C@@H]([C@@H](C)CC)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCCN)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCCN)C(=O)N[C@@H](C(C)C)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCCN)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCCN)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCCN)C(=O)NCC(=O)N[C@@H](CCCN=C)C(=O)N[C@@H](CCCCN)C(=O)O"^^xsd:string ;
    cpp:hasSequence "KIKKVKKKGRKKIKKVKKKGRK"^^xsd:string ;
    cpp:hasUptakeEfficiency "The acid-cleavable Fd-Lip significantly upregulated the uptake (p<0.05 vs cFd-Lip at pH 7.4, p<0.01 vs Fd-Lip). The FA-Lip showed significantly higher uptake than PEG-Lip. Moreover, dual modification of FA and dNP2 further enhanced the cellular uptake, showing synergistic effects."@en,
        "The endocytosis of cFd-Lip (pH 6.8) was higher than that of dNP2-Lip on folate receptor-positive 4T1 cells. The uptake of cFd-Lip by bEnd.3 monolayer cells was 1.01-, 1.26-, 19.90-, and 23.48-fold higher than that of Fd-Lip, dNP2-Lip, FA-Lip and PEG-Lip, respectively."@en,
        "dNP2-EGFP displayed 62.4% EGFP-positive cells, while the cells treated with TAT-EGFP or EGFP alone showed 16.6 and 2.59% EGFP-positive cells,"@en .

