    cpp:hasSequence "AGYLLGKINLKALAALAKKIL"^^xsd:string ;
    cpp:hasUptakeEfficiency "Both TP10(Cf)-NH2 and CIP-CH2CO-TP10(Cf)-NH2  were transported to and accumulated in Candida albicans cells, while CIP(Cf) did not enter these cells. On the other hand, none of the fluorescent probes were taken up by Candida glabrata."@en,
        "Cancer cells after incubation with TAMRA-TP10 + cPt show internalization while lack of internalization in HEL299 cell."@en,
        "Comparable efficiency only in HCT116 cells but not in HT29 cells"@en,
        "Comparable to Penetratin"@en,
        "Comparable to Transportan"@en,
        "Higher uptake efficiency for flourophore"@en,
        "Increased fluorescence of the cells in comparison with the untreated growth controls (or cells treated with fluconazole)"@en,
        "Less than polyarginine and pAntp but equal to Tat"@en,
        "Lower uptake efficiency"@en,
        "PF6/siRNA shows lowest detected GFP signal"@en,
        "PepB2 show greater efficacy than other"@en,
        "TAMRA-TP10 show minimal colocalization (15.84 Â± 5.4%, mean Â± S.E.M.) with secretory granules"@en,
        "TP-10, which showed significantly enhanced translocation in C. glabrata compared to C. albicans."@en,
        "TP10-DA conjugate in brain samples (group 3) was significantly higher (12.07 Î¼g/g wet weight) in comparison to that in group 1 (0.9% NaCl) or group 2 (DA)"@en,
        "Time- and concentration-dependent internalization"@en,
        "successful delivery of splice-switching PMOs"@en .

