    cpp:hasSequence "GRKKRRQRRRPPQ"^^xsd:string ;
    cpp:hasUptakeEfficiency "5 Î¼M TAT-FADD efficiently internalized across the membrane and was retained in the cytosol of HCT116 cells."@en,
        "At 0.25 to 2.5 mM, the membrane permeation property of TATp-D was significantly higher than that of R8, Penetratin, and TATp"@en,
        "Dose-dependent uptake of all proteins"@en,
        "Exhibited a faint fluorescent signal in all experimental conditions"@en,
        "High"@en,
        "Highest values as 46% for Mat-tTAT"@en,
        "Increase of approximately, 85%, 44%, and 131% in the densities of 1, 3, and 6 Î¼mol/L Ab-TrSOD, respectively, in relation to the bands for the enzyme concentration without the Ab peptide,"@en,
        "LMWP group had stronger fluorescence, followed by penetratin, TAT and R8 groups"@en,
        "Less than polyarginine and pAntp but equal to tran"@en,
        "Lowest cellular uptake (â¼23% YOYO-1-positive cells)"@en,
        "Most excellent delivering ability was observed with Pep-1, followed by TAT and AA3H."@en,
        "Penetration efficiency- 475.544875A.U."@en,
        "PepB2 show greater efficacy than other"@en,
        "R8 and Tat increased the uptake of 200-nm nanoparticles by Caco-2 cells to 2.1-3.0 times that was similar or superior than penetratin and PenetraMax"@en,
        "Showed excellent cell uptake"@en,
        "Showed fluorescent signal in more than 10% of the cells."@en,
        "Slight 3-fold increase in luminescence over untreated cells and TAMRA delivery follows P17â>>P11â=âP14â>âP40â=âArg9â>âtatâ=âpenetratin"@en,
        "Slightly higher cellular uptake efficiency of T-hNP than that of hNP in the B16F10 cells."@en,
        "TAT conjugation increased the internalization of gMnSOD in GF-1 cells."@en,
        "TAT modified nanoparticles showed enhanced drug permeation than unmodified"@en,
        "Tat-iCAL36 revealed a ~5.7-fold higher internalization compared to a factor of ~2.0â2.4 for the other CPP-iCAL36 peptides in Calu-3 cells"@en,
        "The 9D11-Tat mAb could successfully enter Huh7 cells, whereas the native 9D11 could not."@en,
        "The cytoplasm was stained by FITC-phalloidin and displayed a green colour and green fluorescent TG was visible in the nuclei of cells after 6 h and 100% cell nuclei stained after 72 h."@en,
        "The uptake efficiency exhibited by formulations containing peptide 6 (DEN-K(GALA)-TAT-K(STR)-CTP) was significantly higher than observed for formulations containing peptide 1 (DEN-K(GALA)-TAT-K(STR))."@en,
        "The uptake of Bom-modified PEG-PCL-Tat micelles was significantly higher than that of PEG-PCL and PEG-PCL-Tat micelles, in C6 cells. However, the bombesin modification conferred no such increase in GRPR-negative COS7 cells."@en,
        "Transduction efficiency near 42% for OBP::Tat in liposomes."@en,
        "Translocation efficacies (mean Â± S.E.M. n = 6) is 4.9 Â± 0.8 for BtnâTatâAvidinâTXR"@en,
        "Translocation efficacy of 1.00 Â± 0.03"@en,
        "Uptake effect of R8 (both L- and D-forms) was stronger than that of Tat"@en,
        "rTAT-Sia10 had the strongest ability to translocate through the cellular membrane into cells"@en .

