    cpp:hasUptakeEfficiency "10 Î¼M STR-His16 with 5 Î¼g/mL lysosomes showed the highest cellular uptake in HT1080 cells and His16-Lyso became localized to endogenous lysosomes after cellular uptake."@en,
        "All polyhistidine-Î¼CL peptides (containing 4â16 histidine residues) showed higher cell permeability than Tat-Î¼CL."@en,
        "Cell-penetrating capacity of the H16-Lipo reached a maximum at approximately 20% modification."@en,
        "H16 peptide showed a 5.45-fold (at pH 6.0) and a 5.36-fold (at pH 7.4) higher cellular uptake than R8 in HepG2 cells and 10.98 and 14.35-fold higher capacities against the RERF-LC-AI and the HT1080 cells, respectively"@en,
        "Long PHPs were trapped in the cell walls of plant cells and showed no cellular uptake in both cells"@en,
        "Maximum penetration among polyhistidine"@en .

